Evoqua Water Technologies > en > About Us > Judd Gregg








Judd Gregg

		Board Member, Former U.S. Senator from New Hampshire / CEO of SIFMA
	






Sen. Gregg is CEO of SIFMA. SIFMA brings together the shared interests of hundreds of securities firms, banks and asset managers who are engaged in communities across the country to raise capital for businesses and provide access to capital to help people on Main Streets across the nation thrive and prosper. America’s success depends on a vibrant financial system; in his role as CEO, Sen. Gregg will promote the role the financial services industry plays in leading economic growth and promoting job creation to the benefit of all Americans.Sen. Gregg served as a United States Senator from 1993 to 2011 and was both Chairman and the Ranking Member of the Senate Budget Committee. Prior to his tenure in the Senate, Sen. Gregg served as Governor of New Hampshire (1989-1993) and as a U.S. Representative (1981-1989).Sen. Gregg is a national leader on fiscal policy, a well-known budget expert and a respected voice on economic and financial regulatory issues. Sen. Gregg served as the chief Republican senate negotiator on the Emergency Economic Stabilization Act of 2008 (TARP) and as a member of the Senate Banking Committee, he Gregg served as one of the principal negotiators working to modernize the U.S. financial regulatory system.Sen. Gregg, along with Sen. Alan Simpson, Erskine Bowles and Gov. Ed Rendell, co-chairs the “Fix the Debt” initiative, which is an effort to develop a comprehensive deficit reduction agreement along the lines of the Simpson-Bowles Commission, on which Sen. Gregg served.In New Hampshire, he is known as champion of land conservation with a more than 30-year commitment to protect the state’s environment. His efforts have helped preserve more than 337,000 acres of sensitive land. As the former Chairman of the Senate Health, Education, Labor and Pensions (HELP) Committee, he has also been a major force for promoting excellence in the higher education community. In 2012, Sen. Gregg was appointed the first Distinguished Fellow at Dartmouth College where he lectures on national governance and history issues.Sen. Gregg attended Columbia University (A.B. 1969), received his J.D. in 1972 from Boston University Law School and his L.L.M. in tax law in 1975.He serves on the Board of Directors of Honeywell Corp. and the InterContinental Exchange (ICE).Sen. Gregg is married to Kathleen MacLellan Gregg. They have three children: Molly, married to John Otter; Sarah, married to William Orum; and Joshua. They also have two grandchildren.



























