                    Current                  


Evoqua Water Technologies LLC

                    Evoqua Water Technologies LLC manufactures and distributes water treatment equipment and other related products. Its products include biological treatment, biosolids treatment, clarification and separation, controls, instrumentation and analysers, dewatering, disinfection, intake, filtration, wastewater and ion exchange. The firm offers filter press equipment, electrocatalytic equipment, media exchange, municipal aftermarket & service, spares and consumables, temporary equipment services. The company serves municipal drinking water, food and beverage, healthcare, municipal wastewater treatment, marine, metals and mining, microelectronics, oil and gas, pharmaceutical, power and remediation markets. Evoqua Water Technologies is headquartered in Warrendale, PA.                  




Independent Director

                    2011 - 2013                  


Intercontinental Exchange Holdings, Inc.

                    Intercontinental Exchange Holdings, Inc. operates as holding company with interest in providing futures exchanges over-the counter markets and derivatives clearing houses and post-trade services. The company was founded by Jeffrey C. Sprecher in May 2000 and is headquartered in Atlanta, GA.                  




Independent Director

                    2011 - Prior                  


Intercontinental Exchange, Inc.

                    Intercontinental Exchange, Inc. engages in the management of online marketplace. It operates through the Trading and Clearing; and Data and Listings segments. The Trading and Clearing segment offers transaction-based executions and clearing activities. The Data and Listings segment includes securities and subscription-based data services. The company was founded by Jeffrey C. Sprecher in May 2000 and is headquartered in Atlanta, GA.                  




Member, Board of Directors

                    Prior                  


FairPoint Communications, Inc.

                    FairPoint Communications, Inc. is a leading communications provider of high-speed Internet access, local and long-distance phone, television and other broadband services to customers in communities across 18 states. Through its fast, reliable data network, FairPoint delivers data and voice networking communications solutions to residential, business and wholesale customers. FairPoint’s resilient IP-based network in northern New England, provides business customers a fast, flexible, affordable Ethernet connection that supports applications like video conferencing and e-learning. FairPoint is traded on the NASDAQ exchange under FRP.                  




